Refining Spot Margins Broadly Down; Utilization Remains at Seasonal 5- year Peak
Spot refining margins were down week on week. Forward curves were also down week on week, but up y/y. See Ex 1.

Jefferies Global Composite 4- Wk Moving Average margin was up \(1\%\) w/w. USGC Cushing 321 margin was down \(15\%\) w/w. WC ANS 321 margin was up \(1\%\) w/w. Mid- Con 321 margin was up \(3\%\) w/w. NWE Brent GC 321 margin was down \(16\%\) w/w. Asia Minas 321 margin was down \(2\%\) w/w.
Please see click [HERE] for full slides, graphically detailing the refining market.
The LINK to our slides where we graphically break down crack spreads, company indicators, forward curves, global refining margins by region and crude type, and RINs.
